{"title_page": "Alabama\u2013Penn State football rivalry", "text_new": "{{Infobox sports rivalry\n| wide                  = yes\n| name                  = Alabama\u2013Penn State football rivalry\n| image                 = \n| image_size            = \n| caption               = \n| team1                 = [[Alabama Crimson Tide football|Alabama Crimson Tide]]\n| team1logo             = Alabama Athletics logo.svg\n| team2                 = [[Penn State Nittany Lions football|Penn State Nittany Lions]]\n| team2logo             = Penn State Athletics wordmark.svg\n| sport                 = \n| firstmeeting          = December 19, 1959<br />Penn State 7, Alabama 0\n| mostrecent            = September 10, 2011<br />Alabama 27, Penn State 11\n| nextmeeting           = \n| total                 = 15\n| series                = Alabama leads, 10\u20135\n| largestvictory        = Alabama, 42\u201321 (1982)<br>Alabama, 24\u20133 (2010)\n| longeststreak         = Alabama, 4 (1975\u201382)\n| longestunbeatenstreak = \n| currentstreak         = Alabama, 2 (2010\u2013)\n| currentunbeatenstreak = \n| trophy                = \n| trophy series         = \n| stadiums              =  \n| map_location          = \n| map_width             = \n| map_label1            = \n| map_mark1             = \n| map_label1_position   = \n| coordinates1          = \n| map_label2            = \n| map_mark2             = \n| map_label2_position   = \n| coordinates2          = \n| map_caption           = \n}}\n{{OSM Location map      \n| nolabels = 1  \n| coord = {{coord|37.01|-82.7}}\n| zoom = 4\n| width = 295 \n| height = 250\n| caption = Locations of Alabama and Penn State\n| mark1 = Red pog.svg\n| label1 = Alabama\n| mark-coord1 = {{coord|33.210833|-87.546111}}\n| label-pos1 = top\n| label-color1 = black\n| mark2 = Blue pog.svg\n| label2 = Penn State\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|40.808623|-77.855536}}\n| label-pos2 = top\n| label-color2 = black\n}}\nThe '''Alabama\u2013Penn State football rivalry''' is an American [[college football]] [[College rivalry#United States|rivalry]] between the [[Alabama Crimson Tide football]] team of the [[University of Alabama]] and [[Penn State Nittany Lions football]] team of [[Pennsylvania State University]].<ref name=\"gs861024\"/> Dormant since 1990, the series was renewed in 2010 in Tuscaloosa and then 2011 in State College.<ref name=\"Rivalry1\"/><ref name=\"Rivalry2\"/><ref name=\"sd100909\"/>\n\n==Notable games==\n\n===1959 Liberty Bowl===\n{{Main|1959 Liberty Bowl}}\n\n===1975 Sugar Bowl===\n{{Main|1975 Sugar Bowl}}\n\n===1979 Sugar Bowl===\n{{Main|1979 Sugar Bowl}}\nAlabama scored in the second quarter, then Penn State answered in the third, then Alabama took a 14\u20137 lead on a touchdown set up by a 62-yard punt return.<ref name=\"A1979\"/> Penn State had a chance to tie in the fourth, but [[Chuck Fusina]] threw an [[interception]] into the Alabama end zone. Then the Crimson Tide had a chance to put the game away, but [[fumble]]d the football back to Penn State at the Nittany Lion 19-yard-line with four minutes to go. Penn State drove to a first and goal at the Alabama eight. On third and goal from the one, Fusina asked Bama linebacker [[Marty Lyons]] \"What do you think we should do?\", and Lyons answered \"You'd better pass.\" On third down, Penn State was stopped inches short of the goal line.<ref name=\"A1979\"/> On fourth down, Penn State was stopped again, Barry Krauss meeting [[Mike Guman]] and throwing him back for no gain.<ref name=\"A1979\"/> Alabama held on for a 14\u20137 victory.<ref name=\"A1979\"/>\n\n== Game results ==\n{{sports rivalry series table\n| series_summary = yes\n| legend_tie_text =\n| team1 = Alabama\n| team1style = {{NCAA color cell|Alabama Crimson Tide}}\n| team2 = Penn State\n| team2style = {{NCAA color cell|Penn State Nittany Lions}}\n\n| [[1959 Liberty Bowl|December 19, 1959]]  | Philadelphia, PA | #12 Penn State | 7 | #10 Alabama | 0\n| [[1975 Sugar Bowl|December 31, 1975]]  | New Orleans, LA | #3 Alabama | 13 | #7 Penn State | 6\n| [[1979 Sugar Bowl|January 1, 1979]]  | New Orleans, LA | #2 Alabama | 14 | #1 Penn State | 7\n| November 14, 1981 | State College, PA | #6 Alabama | 31 | #5 Penn State | 16 \n| October 9, 1982 | Birmingham, AL | #4 Alabama | 42 | #3 Penn State | 21 \n| October 8, 1983 | State College, PA | Penn State | 34 | #3 Alabama | 28 \n| October 13, 1984 | Tuscaloosa, AL | Alabama | 6 | #11 Penn State | 0 \n| October 12, 1985 | State College, PA | #8 Penn State | 19 | #10 Alabama | 17 \n| October 25, 1986 | Tuscaloosa, AL | #6 Penn State | 23 | #2 Alabama | 3 \n| September 12, 1987 | State College, PA | #19 Alabama | 24 | #11 Penn State | 13 \n| October 22, 1988 | Birmingham, AL | Alabama | 8 | Penn State | 3 \n| October 28, 1989 | State College, PA | #6 Alabama | 17 | #14 Penn State | 16 \n| October 27, 1990 | Tuscaloosa, AL | Penn State | 9 | Alabama | 0 \n| September 11, 2010 | Tuscaloosa, AL | #1 Alabama | 24 | #18 Penn State | 3 \n| September 10, 2011 | State College, PA | #3 Alabama | 27 | #23 Penn State | 11 \n}}\nSeries record source: ''2011 Alabama Football Media Guide'',<ref name=bamamediaguide>''[http://www.rolltide.com/sports/m-footbl/media-guide.html  2011 Alabama Football Media Guide] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710010929/http://www.rolltide.com/sports/m-footbl/media-guide.html |date=2011-07-10 }}'', University of Alabama Department of Intercollegiate Athletics, Tuscaloosa, Alabama, pp. 176&ndash;195 (2011).  Retrieved November 28, 2011.</ref> and College Football Data Warehouse.<ref>College Football Data Warehouse, [http://cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_ia/sec/alabama/opponents_records.php?teamid=2514  Alabama vs Penn State] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111023101753/http://cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_ia/sec/alabama/opponents_records.php?teamid=2514 |date=2011-10-23 }}.  Retrieved November 28, 2011.</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of NCAA college football rivalry games]]\n\n=